1. Aggregate Functions
COUNT() – Returns the number of rows
SUM() – Returns the sum of a numeric column
AVG() – Returns the average value of a numeric column
MIN() – Returns the minimum value in a column
MAX() – Returns the maximum value in a column
GROUP_CONCAT() – Concatenates values from multiple rows (MySQL)

2. String Functions

CONCAT() – Joins two or more strings
SUBSTRING() – Extracts a part of a string
LENGTH() – Returns the length of a string
LOWER() – Converts a string to lowercase
UPPER() – Converts a string to uppercase
TRIM() – Removes leading and trailing spaces
REPLACE() – Replaces occurrences of a substring
LEFT() – Returns a specified number of characters from the start
RIGHT() – Returns a specified number of characters from the end

3. Date & Time Functions

NOW() – Returns the current timestamp
CURDATE() – Returns the current date
CURTIME() – Returns the current time
DATEADD() – Adds an interval to a date (SQL Server)
DATEDIFF() – Returns the difference between two dates
EXTRACT() – Extracts part of a date (year, month, day, etc.)

4. Mathematical Functions

ROUND() – Rounds a number to a specified decimal place
CEIL() – Returns the smallest integer greater than or equal to a number
FLOOR() – Returns the largest integer less than or equal to a number
ABS() – Returns the absolute value of a number
MOD() – Returns the remainder of a division

5. Conditional & Control Functions

CASE – Performs conditional logic in SQL queries
IF() – Performs conditional logic (MySQL)
COALESCE() – Returns the first non-null value in a list
NULLIF() – Returns NULL if two values are equal


6. Advanced Aggregate Functions
STDDEV() – Returns the standard deviation of a numeric column
VARIANCE() – Returns the variance of a numeric column
PERCENTILE_CONT() – Calculates continuous percentile (PostgreSQL, SQL Server)
PERCENTILE_DISC() – Calculates discrete percentile
MEDIAN() – Returns the median value (some databases)

7. More String Functions

CHAR_LENGTH() – Returns the length of a string in characters
POSITION() – Finds the position of a substring in a string
LPAD() – Pads a string from the left (MySQL, PostgreSQL)
RPAD() – Pads a string from the right
FORMAT() – Formats numbers with locale-specific settings
ASCII() – Returns ASCII code of the first character
CHAR() – Converts ASCII code to character
REVERSE() – Reverses a string


8. More Date & Time Functions
DATE_FORMAT() – Formats a date (MySQL)
TO_DATE() – Converts a string to a date
TO_CHAR() – Converts a date to a string
LAST_DAY() – Returns the last day of the month
ADD_MONTHS() – Adds months to a date
NEXT_DAY() – Returns the next specified weekday


9. Window (Analytic) Functions

RANK() – Assigns a rank to each row with gaps
DENSE_RANK() – Assigns a rank to each row without gaps
ROW_NUMBER() – Assigns a unique row number
NTILE(n) – Divides rows into n equal parts
LEAD() – Returns the value from the next row
LAG() – Returns the value from the previous row
FIRST_VALUE() – Returns the first value in a window
LAST_VALUE() – Returns the last value in a window

10. More Mathematical Functions

LOG() – Returns the logarithm of a number
EXP() – Returns e raised to the power of a number
POWER() – Raises a number to a given power
SIGN() – Returns the sign of a number (+1, 0, -1)
RADIANS() – Converts degrees to radians
DEGREES() – Converts radians to degrees

11. More Conditional & Null Handling Functions

GREATEST() – Returns the largest value in a list
LEAST() – Returns the smallest value in a list
IFNULL() – Returns a replacement value if NULL (MySQL)
ISNULL() – Checks if a value is NULL (SQL Server)
NVL() – Replaces NULL with a specified value (Oracle)
